<title>USA: Quaker to seek more shr buyback authority.</title>
<headline>Quaker to seek more shr buyback authority.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1997-04-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Quaker Oats Co said Wednesday it will seek additional share repurchase authority in the future, after it resumes its existing share buyback activity.</p>
<p>Quaker Chairman William Smithburg said the food and beverage company has about 3.5 million shares to be repurchased under a past authorization.</p>
<p>&quot;We plan to go in for more (share repurchase) authority as we move along,&quot; Smithburg told a teleconference.  </p>
<p>Quaker suspended its share repurchase program in summer 1994.</p>
<p>Quaker officials declined to speculate how many shares it would seek to repurchase under a new authorization.</p>
<p>((Reuters Chicago Newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
